- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper mentions tuning hyper-parameters of machine learning algorithms, which is a common task in AI.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper proposes a new tool for automating the provisioning and tuning of data analytic applications, which involves software engineering principles.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the search space of different configurations for data analytic jobs, which involves algorithmic optimization.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve programming language-specific optimizations for data analytic frameworks.
